    dc:title "Thoridae (Crustacea: Decapoda) can penetrate the Abyss: a new species of Lebbeus from the Sea of Okhotsk, representing the deepest record of the family" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669917>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669919>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669925>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669923>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669927>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669929> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669917>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Lebbeus sokhobio sp. nov., general view, ♀ from st. 4-3 (paratype, ZMMU Ma6097) and ♂ from st. 4-9 (paratype, SMF 51579)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3669917/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669919>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Lebbeus sokhobio sp. nov., ♀ from st. 4-3 (paratype, ZMMU Ma6097) (A–I) and ♂ from st. 4-10 (paratype, MIMB 39426) (J–K). A–B. Anterior part of carapace. C. Abdominal pleonites IV–V, lateral view. D–E. Antennula. F. Antenna. G. Telson and uropods. H. Distal margin of telson. I. Distolateral margin of exopod. J. Endopod of pleopod I. K. Endopod of pleopod II." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3669919/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669925>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Lebbeus sokhobio sp. nov., carapaces. A. ♂ from st. 4-9 (paratype, SMF 51579). B. ♀ from st. 1-10 (holotype, ZMMU Ma5836). C. ♀ from st. 7-12 (paratype, MIMB 39427). D. ♀ from st. 4-9 (paratype, SMF 51579). E. ♂ from st. 1-10 (paratype, ZMMU Ma6096). F. ♀ from st. 4-3 (paratype, ZMMU Ma6097). G. ♂ from st. 4-10 (paratype, MIMB 39426). H. Juvenile from st. 4-10 (paratype, MIMB 39426). I. ♂ from st. 4-10 (paratype, MIMB 39426)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3669925/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669923>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Lebbeus sokhobio sp. nov., ♀ from st. 4-3 (paratype, ZMMU Ma6097) (A–H, J–K, M) and ♂ from st. 4-9 (paratype, SMF 51579) (I, L). A. Basal segments of pereiopods I–III. B. Maxilliped III. C. Antepenultimate segment of maxilliped III. D. Pereiopod I. E. Chela of pereiopod I. F. Proximal segments of pereiopod I. G. Pereiopod II. H. Pereiopod III. I. Merus of pereiopod III. J. Dactylus of pereiopod III. K. Pereiopod IV. L. Merus of pereiopod IV. M. Pereiopod V." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3669923/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669927>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Lebbeus sokhobio sp. nov., ♂ from st. 4-9 (paratype, SMF 51579), live coloration." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3669927/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669929>
    dc:description "Fig. 7. Phylogenetic relationships within Thoridae (Hippolyte Leach, 1814 as outgroup) based on COI mtDNA gene markers. Bootstrap support (> 50%) is shown by the numbers along the branches (BA/ML analysis). Line thickness is also correlated with support values." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3669929/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

